s and institutional records paint a vivid picture of a world in which both middle-class and working-class American Jewish women were consistently andpublicly engaged in all the major issues of their day and worked closely with their non-Jewish counterparts on behalf of activist causes.This extraordinarily well researched volume makes a unique contribution to the study of modern women's history, modern Jewish history, and the history of American social movements.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jun 2020) 0aJewish womenxPolitical activityxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aJewish womenxPolitical activityzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish womenxSocial conditionsx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aJewish womenzUnited StatesxPolitical activityxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish womenzUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aWomen and peacexHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aWomen and peacezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenxPolitical activityxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aWomenxPolitical activityzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenxSocial conditionsx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aWomenxSuffragexHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aWomenxSuffragezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenzUnited StatesxPolitical activityxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenzUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814749463423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814749463.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aE